.TH "phy_modify_mmd" 9 "phy_modify_mmd" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
phy_modify_mmd \- Convenience function for modifying a register on MMD
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" phy_modify_mmd
.BI "(struct phy_device *phydev "  ","
.BI "int devad "  ","
.BI "u32 regnum "  ","
.BI "u16 mask "  ","
.BI "u16 set "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phydev" 12
the phy_device struct
.IP "devad" 12
the MMD containing register to modify
.IP "regnum" 12
register number to modify
.IP "mask" 12
bit mask of bits to clear
.IP "set" 12
new value of bits set in mask to write to \fIregnum\fP
.SH "NOTE"
MUST NOT be called from interrupt context,
because the bus read/write functions may wait for an interrupt
to conclude the operation.
